A river otter has attacked two teenage cousins as they played on a rope swing in a US river, in scenes described by their grandmother as 'like something out of Jaws'.

Kierra Clark, 13, and Matalyn Longtain, 11, were playing in the Kalama River near their grandparents' home in Washington state when Kierra felt a sharp pain in her leg.

When she looked back she saw a river otter glaring back at her with 'huge eyes' popping out of the water and teeth she described as 'sharp and long'.

