As they swam faster they continued to feel bites on their legs and ankles. Kicking their assailants away they clambered onto a float of canoes where they were dragged to the shore by their grandfather Bob Schlecht Jr. and his friend Fred Palmer.

'It was terrifying,' Kierra’s grandmother, Arlita Schlecht, who helped in the rescue told Katu.com. 'I could see she had blood streaming down her leg. (It was like) a scene out of Jaws.'

